            </item>
            <item>
             <widget class="QComboBox" name="plotTypeComBox">
              <property name="maximumSize">
               <size>
                <width>115</width>
                <height>16777215</height>
               </size>
              </property>
              <property name="toolTip">
               <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;Choose the plot type for illustration of the order parameter (OP) data values x,y (and z, depending).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;2D Density&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;A 2-dimensional histogram, where data set is mapped to a X*X grid (X = grid resolution), and density of each gridpoint is mapped to a color gradient.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;2D Density (weighted)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Same as above, but accepted paths (if chosen) will be re-weighted statistically (re-counted) before plotting.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;3D Surface&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;An interpolated surface of x-, y-, and z-data mapped to a X*X grid and colored by a gradient of the interpolated z-values of the grid.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;2D Contour&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;An interpolated contour plot of x-, y- and z-data mapped to a X*X grid and colored by a gradient of the interpolated z-values of the grid&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;2D Contour (filled)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Same as above, but contour lines are now filled in, giving a rough 2-dimensional surface of the z-values.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;3D Contour&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Same exact plot as the 2-dimensional, but projected in 3 dimensions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;3D Contour (filled)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Same exact plot as the 2-dimensional, but projected in 3 dimensions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;2D Scatter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;A 2-dimensional scatter plot of x-, y- and z-data. The z-data is mapped to a color gradient. &lt;br/&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:600; font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;NB!&lt;/span&gt; This plot shows &lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;all&lt;/span&gt; data points, and will therefore be much more resource-demanding than the other plots.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;3D Scatter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Same exact plot as the 2-dimensional, but projected in 3 dimensions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
              </property>
              <item>
