                <property name="toolTip">
                 <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;Choice of analysis method to utilize on the chosen data.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Kmeans&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perform Kmeans clustering with a selected amount of clusters. This technique will cluster the data to the nearest centroid using a euclidean distance measure which aims to minimize the within-cluster variation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;PCA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perform principal component analysis with a chosen amount of components. The function will compute the analysis and store the data to a hdf file. The data stored is the scores of the principal components availeable with the keyword: PC. The loadings availeable through the keyword: loadings. The correlation matrix is availeable through the keyword: correlation_matrix, and the explained variance for the components is availeable through: explained and the simulation data through: sim_data&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The scores plot from the first two components, loadings matrix and the explained variance will also be plotted. &lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;NB: &lt;/span&gt;The amount of components cannot exceed the amount of variables availeable for plotting except time and cycle.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Hierarchical&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hierarchical clustering with a euclidean distance measure and an average linkage criterion between clusters. &lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;NB:&lt;/span&gt; This method is sensitive to large data, and may not be possible depending on the size of the dataset.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Gaussian Mixture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perform a gaussian mixture clustering with a selected amount of clusters. This method is beneficial as it accounts for the variance meaning that this model is suited for clusters of different shapes. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Spectral&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spectral clustering will turn the clustering problem into a graph partitioning problem. Useful when the structure of the individual clusters is highly non-convex or more generally when a measure of the center and spread of the cluster is not a suitable description of the complete cluster. The graph is constructed based on the k-nearest-neighbour, with 30 neighbours.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
                </property>
                <item>
                 <property name="text">
                  <string>Kmeans</string>
                 </property>
                </item>
                <item>
                 <property name="text">
                  <string>Hierarchical</string>
                 </property>
                </item>
                <item>
                 <property name="text">
                  <string>Gaussian Mixture</string>
                 </property>
                </item>
                <item>
                 <property name="text">
                  <string>Spectral</string>
                 </property>
                </item>
               </widget>
              </item>
